<br>
A)  It cant be dispelled... ever.  Jboots and Sow Can,  not sure about horses..  they are a buff though..  Someone who has one could probably tell you.<br>
<br>
B) Jboot/Sow Can't be cast indoors.  Run Speed.. is all the time.  Great for pullers... keeps them ahead of a lot of mobs instead of taking a beating on the way back.  Great for anyone moving in a dungeon setting.  Its not often that convenient to &quot;just pop outdoors&quot; to recast jboots/sow.  Especially in the 50+ game.<br>
<br>
C) Horses while nice (especially for casters because they can med standing essentially) are at their lowest version, slow as Jboots, take time to get running full speed, and time to stop (not good for trying to cast a spell), Eat your food, are even more limited about where they can be used (not in the water, they poof when you go indoors), are bloody Expensive, and make it horribly hard to target anything unless you switch to a different view.<br>
<br>
D)  Ya gotta spend your points somewhere to get to Archetypes and Class Abilities later on.  And most people in thier 50's usually dont need too much help with stat boosts.  And personally I'd rather get gear to do that then spend aprox 6 levels worth of xp on wisdom/resists/ect just to get to my Archetypes Abilities.<br>
<br>
